blog.description: A lone fan fiction writer, and an aspiring poet. Has been a fan of BTS since 2013, and avidly writes about them.

title: BTS Writing Prompt
body:
Based off the song, Six Feet Under by Billie Eilish 

Taehyung leaves Jungkook for alcohol. Drinking every day and every night, Taehyung is almost always in a drunken stupor. Every time he gets drunk, he remembers Jungkook and how he left him. But he knows he shouldn’t go back to him, it wouldn’t end well for them both of them. But Taehyung wants Jungkook to tell him that he should come back to him. But their love is six feet under, there’s no saving their love. Jungkook erases almost all of Taehyung from his memory but he sometimes retraces the places Taehyung touched him. He blows the memories away like smoke, wondering if Taehyung would die carelessly from all the alcohol. Soon, Taehyung dies from liver problems caused by all the alcohol and Jungkook follows him into the afterlife by swallowing pills. They both meet on the other side, on the clouds. As their bodies turn cold as night, they are lowered into graves, right next to each other. Roses are planted around their graves, with more roses blooming from seeds. Their graves are watered by the rain as Taehyung tries to make up for lost time while Jungkook turns him away, always blowing him off like smoke in the air.

body:
Bad Time For A Good Time -

Chapter 9: Snakes In The Grass.

Jungkook x Reader, Namjoon x Reader

Warnings: Implication of sex, and cursing.

Prev| Next

Jeon Jungkook is the ultimate bachelor; guarded, angry, rich, body count that puts the numeric system to shame, and aimless - what else could a girl want? You’ve been working in the same dead end job, hoping it would get you somewhere. You finally have your foot in the door, and the person you need to win over is slamming your foot out. What can you do?

I will be posting every day at 10am AKST! I don’t have links included in my posts, because tumblr still messes with it, but all the links are in my masterlist! 🖤

Post time per time zone:

AKST - 10am

PST - 11am

MST - 12pm

CST - 1pm

EST - 2pm
